US President Donald Trump said on Monday he was unsure if he would meet with Russian leader Vladimir Putin during a visit to Paris this month, but he will meet him at the Nov. 30-Dec. 1 summit of the Group of 20 nations in Argentina. “We haven’t set anything up yet. We don’t know that that’s going to be the right place. I’m going to be in Paris for other reasons. But we will be meeting at the G20,” Trump said at Joint Base Andrews before leaving on a campaign trip. ALSO READ:

